You need to think of how you want to reduce the list of `Position` values into a single `Position`. Then you can use [Stream.reduce][1] to convert a `Stream&lt;CompletableFuture&lt;Position&gt;&gt;` into a `CompletableFuture&lt;Position&gt;` by lifting that reduction function into the stream: 

    static &lt;T&gt; CompletableFuture&lt;T&gt; reduce(
            Stream&lt;CompletableFuture&lt;T&gt;&gt; futures,
            T identity,
            BinaryOperator&lt;T&gt; accumulator)
    {
        return futures.reduce(
            completedFuture(identity),
            (f1, f2) -&gt;
                f1.thenCompose(s1 -&gt;
                f2.thenApply(s2 -&gt;
                    accumulator.apply(s1, s2))));
    }

For example, to concatenate some strings wrapped in `CompletableFuture`s you would do

    Stream&lt;CompletableFuture&lt;String&gt;&gt; futures = Stream.of(
        completedFuture(&quot;A&quot;),
        completedFuture(&quot;mouse&quot;),
        completedFuture(&quot;took&quot;),
        completedFuture(&quot;a&quot;),
        completedFuture(&quot;stroll&quot;));

    System.out.println(
        reduce(futures, &quot;&quot;, (s1, s2) -&gt; s1 + &quot; &quot; + s2).get());

Which prints &quot;A mouse took a stroll&quot;  

  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/12/docs/api/java.base/java/util/stream/Stream.html#reduce(T,java.util.function.BinaryOperator)

