You need to make the method generic, for example:

    public &lt;E&gt; int[] computeDepths(AbstractTree&lt;E&gt; tree, int n) {
        // Code
    }

Either the method or the class needs to be generic in order to use generic types within them.

When code calls the method, you either need the compiler to work out the type for you (for example, based on the specific abstract tree that is passed) or you need to specify it where it can&#39;t be inferred.

